<p><strong>Expert Verified</strong> — Written by Stacc Editorial. 12 AI writing tools tested and benchmarked for cost, output, and total spend. Pricing verified May 2026. We publish 3,500+ SEO blogs every month across 70+ industries.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>AI writing tools pricing in 2026 is a moving target. The sticker price ranges from $9 per month to $249 per month, and the gap between what you pay and what you actually spend is wider than ever. Most pricing pages hide credits, seats, word caps, and renewal jumps in the fine print. This guide pulls every plan into the open.</p>
<p>The cost of picking wrong is not small. A $49 tool that you outgrow in 60 days costs you the subscription, the migration, the lost content, and the time your team spent learning it. Stack that mistake across 12 months and you are out $1,500 plus the rankings you never built.</p>
<p>We benchmarked 12 of the most popular AI writing tools by what they cost, what you actually get, and what 30 articles per month works out to under each plan. We also include the hidden line items most comparisons skip: writer time, editor time, and the cost of staying inside one tool versus moving up a tier.</p>
<p>We publish 30 SEO articles per month for businesses across 70+ industries. We test these tools because we use them, and we compete with some of them. Here is what we found.</p>
<p>Here is what you will learn:</p>
<ul>
<li>Real pricing for 12 AI writing tools, verified May 2026</li>
<li>Which tools have genuinely free plans and which run a free trial</li>
<li>The hidden cost of every "starting at" plan</li>
<li>A side-by-side cost-per-article comparison</li>
<li>Which tool fits your budget, team, and content goals</li>
</ul>
<h2>AI Writing Tool Pricing at a Glance</h2>
<p>Here is the full lineup at the price you actually pay on an annual plan. Most of these tools charge 20% to 30% more if you pay month to month.</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" alt="Pricing tiers across 12 AI writing tools showing free, budget, mid-tier, and premium categories" src="/images/blog/ai-writing-tools-pricing-tiers.png" /></p>
<p>Four tiers cover the entire market. The free tier is real for ChatGPT, Claude, Rytr, and Copy.ai, but every free plan has output caps that make daily content production impossible. The budget tier ($9 to $29 per month) is the sweet spot for solo writers and bloggers. The mid-tier ($39 to $79 per month) adds SEO features, team seats, and brand voice tools. The premium tier ($89 and up) pushes into agency-grade workflows with multi-seat plans and SERP-grounded editing.</p>
<p>Pricing has actually dropped 15% across this category since 2024, driven by competition from open-weight models and <a href="https://openai.com/api/pricing/">OpenAI's own pricing pressure</a>. That is good news for buyers, but it also means most "best of" articles you read are quoting prices that are 12 months out of date.</p>
