<h2>7. Writesonic — Best AI Writing Tool for SEO Content</h2>
<p>Writesonic starts at $16 per month for the Unlimited Lite plan, with the Standard plan at $39 per month and Professional at $199 per month. The free plan offers 25 credits worth about 10,000 words.</p>
<h3>What It Does Well</h3>
<p>Writesonic is the most SEO-aware tool in the budget tier. The AI Article Writer 6.0 pulls live SERP data, generates outlines from top-ranking pages, and scores drafts against your target keyword. You get this on the $39 Standard plan, which undercuts Surfer and Jasper by 50% or more.</p>
<p>The unlimited word output on every paid plan is rare. Most competitors gate words behind credits or upgrades. Writesonic gives you unlimited GPT-4o output starting at $16 per month, which makes the per-article cost effectively zero once you commit.</p>
<blockquote>
<p><strong>Our Take:</strong> Writesonic is the right answer for SEO-focused bloggers and small marketing teams who want SERP grounding without the Surfer price tag. The article quality lags Claude for nuance and Jasper for marketing voice, but the SEO features close the gap for ranking content. We have ranked posts written in Writesonic that we could not have written as fast in Claude.</p>
</blockquote>
<h3>Where It Falls Short</h3>
<p>The interface tries to do too much. Writesonic has chat, article generation, image generation, audio, and a botsonic chatbot builder — most of which dilute the focus. The free plan is generous for testing but useless for production. Customer support is slow.</p>
<h3>Pricing</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Free:</strong> 25 credits, GPT-3.5 only</li>
<li><strong>Lite:</strong> $16 per month — unlimited words, basic features</li>
<li><strong>Standard:</strong> $39 per month — SEO mode, factual writing</li>
<li><strong>Professional:</strong> $199 per month — 3 seats, advanced SEO</li>
<li><strong>Enterprise:</strong> Custom — 50+ seats, white-label</li>
</ul>
<h3>Who Should Use Writesonic</h3>
<p><strong>Strong fit:</strong>
- SEO bloggers wanting SERP-grounded drafts
- Small marketing teams on a budget
- Anyone replacing a $90+ tool with something cheaper</p>
<p><strong>Probably not right for:</strong>
- Brand-voice-heavy content
- Long-form thought leadership
- Teams who already have a strong writer</p>
<p>For a deeper look at Writesonic specifically, see our <a href="/reviews/writesonic/">Writesonic review</a> or compare it against alternatives in our <a href="/alternatives/writesonic/">Writesonic alternatives</a> guide.</p>
<h2>8. Frase — Best AI Tool for SEO Content Briefs</h2>
<p>Frase starts at $45 per month for the Basic plan and $115 per month for the Premium plan. There is no free plan, but a 5-day trial for $1 is available.</p>
<h3>What It Does Well</h3>
<p>Frase is built for SEO content briefs. You enter a target keyword, Frase analyzes the top 20 SERP results, and you get a brief with headings, questions, statistics, and average word count. The content editor scores your draft against the SERP in real time.</p>
<p>The brief-first workflow is the differentiator. Most AI tools generate content from a prompt. Frase generates a brief first, which makes the resulting content more SEO-aligned because it is grounded in what is ranking.</p>
<blockquote>
<p><strong>Our Take:</strong> Frase is the tool we recommend when a client wants to build content briefs in-house instead of hiring an SEO strategist. The brief quality is consistently better than what an entry-level SEO would produce. The downside is the 30-document cap on Basic — you hit it fast if you publish more than 4 articles per week.</p>
</blockquote>
<h3>Where It Falls Short</h3>
<p>The 30-document cap on Basic forces you up to Premium fast. The AI writing inside Frase is weaker than dedicated tools like Jasper or Claude — most teams use Frase for briefs and write in another tool. The interface has a learning curve. Pricing for add-on seats is high.</p>
<h3>Pricing</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Basic:</strong> $45 per month — 30 documents per month</li>
<li><strong>Team:</strong> $115 per month — unlimited documents, 3 seats</li>
<li><strong>Pro Add-On:</strong> $35 per month — unlimited AI writing</li>
<li><strong>Free trial:</strong> 5-day trial for $1</li>
</ul>
<h3>Who Should Use Frase</h3>
<p><strong>Strong fit:</strong>
- SEO teams building content briefs
- Marketing managers who outsource writing
- Anyone optimizing existing content against SERPs</p>
<p><strong>Probably not right for:</strong>
- Solo bloggers (the brief-first workflow is overkill)
- Teams who write more than 30 articles per month
- Anyone who wants generation, not briefs</p>
<p>See our full <a href="/reviews/frase/">Frase review</a> for a deeper analysis or check our <a href="/alternatives/frase/">Frase alternatives</a> page for cheaper options.</p>
<h2>9. Jasper — Best AI Writing Tool for Marketing Teams</h2>
<p>Jasper starts at $49 per month for the Creator plan and $125 per month for the Pro plan. Custom pricing applies to the Business and Enterprise plans, which typically run $500 to $2,000 per month.</p>
<h3>What It Does Well</h3>
<p>Jasper's brand voice training is the strongest in the category. You upload existing content, Jasper learns your tone, and every output adopts that voice. The 100+ marketing-specific templates cover everything from cold emails to YouTube descriptions to ad copy.</p>
<p>Jasper Canvas is the workspace where the tool earns its premium price. You can run multi-step campaigns — outline, draft, edit, repurpose — across formats in one project. The Knowledge Assets feature lets you store product facts, company info, and approved messaging that every output respects.</p>
<blockquote>
<p><strong>Our Take:</strong> Jasper is overkill for solo writers and a strong value for marketing teams. The brand voice feature alone justifies $49 per month if you produce content for multiple channels. The downside is that the Creator plan locks the best features behind Pro — Knowledge Assets, campaigns, and the image generator are all Pro-only.</p>
</blockquote>
<h3>Where It Falls Short</h3>
<p>The Creator plan at $49 per month does not include the features Jasper markets the hardest — Knowledge Assets, campaigns, brand voices (multiple), and Jasper Art. Pro at $125 per month per seat scales fast for teams. The output quality has slipped behind Claude for long-form work since 2024. No SERP grounding without a Surfer integration.</p>
<h3>Pricing</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Creator:</strong> $49 per month — 1 seat, 1 brand voice, basic features</li>
<li><strong>Pro:</strong> $69 per month annual or $125 per month monthly — Knowledge Assets, campaigns, 3 brand voices</li>
<li><strong>Business:</strong> Custom (typically $500+/mo) — multi-seat, SSO, API</li>
<li><strong>Free trial:</strong> 7-day free trial</li>
</ul>
<h3>Who Should Use Jasper</h3>
<p><strong>Strong fit:</strong>
- Marketing teams managing multiple brands or channels
- Agencies producing content for multiple clients
- Anyone where brand voice consistency is non-negotiable</p>
<p><strong>Probably not right for:</strong>
- Solo bloggers or small businesses
- Anyone needing SEO-first content
- Teams that just want output (Jasper's complexity slows you down)</p>
<p>See our full <a href="/reviews/jasper-ai/">Jasper AI review</a> and our <a href="/alternatives/jasper/">Jasper alternatives</a> guide for cheaper picks.</p>
<h2>10. Copy.ai — Best AI Tool for Sales and Workflow Automation</h2>
<p>Copy.ai starts at $49 per month for the Starter plan, $249 per month for the Advanced plan, and $1,000+ per month for sales workflow automation. The free plan gives you 2,000 words per month.</p>
<h3>What It Does Well</h3>
<p>Copy.ai pivoted hard into sales workflow automation in 2024. The platform now combines AI writing with multi-step workflows that pull data from CRMs, enrich leads, and generate outreach copy. The Advanced plan includes 5 seats, which works out to $50 per user — the cheapest team plan on this list at that scale.</p>
<p>The free plan is genuinely useful. You get 2,000 words per month with access to GPT-4 and most templates. For occasional users, that is enough for a few short pieces.</p>
<blockquote>
<p><strong>Our Take:</strong> Copy.ai is no longer competing for the blog content market. The platform is best understood as a sales automation tool that happens to write copy. If you run a sales team, the workflow automation justifies the price. If you are a content marketer, the $49 Starter plan feels overpriced compared to Writesonic.</p>
</blockquote>
<h3>Where It Falls Short</h3>
<p>The blog content output quality lags Claude and Jasper for long-form work. The interface complexity has grown with the sales pivot — content marketers now have to ignore 70% of the platform. The $1,000+ Workflows plan is a wall most small businesses cannot afford to test.</p>
<h3>Pricing</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Free:</strong> 2,000 words per month, 1 seat</li>
<li><strong>Starter:</strong> $49 per month — unlimited words, 1 seat</li>
<li><strong>Advanced:</strong> $249 per month — 5 seats, workflows</li>
<li><strong>Workflows:</strong> $1,000+/month — sales automation, multi-seat</li>
</ul>
<h3>Who Should Use Copy.ai</h3>
<p><strong>Strong fit:</strong>
- Sales teams running outbound at scale
- Revenue ops teams enriching CRM data
- Agencies running multi-client outreach</p>
<p><strong>Probably not right for:</strong>
- Content marketers (better options at this price)
- Solo bloggers
- SEO-focused workflows</p>
<p>See our <a href="/reviews/copy-ai/">Copy.ai review</a> for more or check <a href="/alternatives/copy-ai/">Copy.ai alternatives</a> for cheaper options.</p>
<h2>11. Surfer SEO — Best Premium AI Tool for SERP-Grounded Writing</h2>
<p>Surfer SEO starts at $89 per month for the Essential plan and $129 per month for the Scale plan. There is no free plan and no free trial — you have to commit to a month to test it.</p>
<h3>What It Does Well</h3>
<p>Surfer's content editor is the gold standard for SERP grounding. You enter a target keyword, Surfer analyzes the top-ranking pages, and you write inside an editor that scores your draft in real time against word count, keyword density, heading structure, and topic coverage.</p>
<p>The Surfer AI feature added in 2024 generates full first drafts that hit Surfer's own scoring rubric. You can publish-ready in under 20 minutes for most keywords. The integration with Jasper, ChatGPT, and Google Docs means you can write anywhere and bring the score with you.</p>
<blockquote>
<p><strong>Our Take:</strong> Surfer is the tool we recommend when a client has a content team and just needs SERP guidance. The scoring is the most accurate in the category — we have seen multiple Stacc-written articles hit a 75+ Surfer score and rank in the top 10 within 90 days. The downside is the price. $89 per month is the entry point, and the Scale plan jumps to $129 for features most teams will outgrow.</p>
</blockquote>
<h3>Where It Falls Short</h3>
<p>The 30-article cap on Essential is generous but real. Pricing jumps sharply from Essential to Scale to Enterprise. There is no free plan or trial — you commit a month to test. The AI writing inside Surfer is weaker than the SEO scoring, so most teams generate elsewhere and paste into Surfer.</p>
<h3>Pricing</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Essential:</strong> $89 per month — 30 articles, 1 seat</li>
<li><strong>Scale:</strong> $129 per month — 100 articles, 5 seats, AI generation</li>
<li><strong>Enterprise:</strong> Custom — multi-seat, SSO, white-label</li>
<li><strong>Free trial:</strong> None (7-day money-back guarantee)</li>
</ul>
<h3>Who Should Use Surfer SEO</h3>
<p><strong>Strong fit:</strong>
- Content teams optimizing for SERPs
- SEO agencies managing client articles
- Anyone with a writer who needs scoring guidance</p>
<p><strong>Probably not right for:</strong>
- Solo bloggers (the price does not pencil)
- Anyone who wants the AI to do the writing
- Budget-conscious teams (Writesonic does 70% for half the cost)</p>
