<h2>Hidden Costs Most Pricing Pages Hide</h2>
<p>Every pricing page in this category buries something. Here are the 5 most common traps.</p>
<p><strong>1. Annual versus monthly billing gap.</strong> Most "starting at $X per month" prices assume annual billing. Pay month to month and you pay 20% to 30% more. Jasper's Pro plan jumps from $69 to $125 if you pay monthly. Writesonic's Lite jumps from $16 to $20.</p>
<p><strong>2. Premium model gating.</strong> The cheaper plans often lock you out of GPT-4o or Claude 3.5. Rytr Unlimited gives you GPT-4o at $9, but ChatGPT free caps you on it. Writesonic Lite uses GPT-3.5 by default.</p>
<p><strong>3. Seat costs.</strong> Team plans rarely scale linearly. Jasper Pro is $125 per seat. Copy.ai Advanced is $249 for 5 seats ($50 per user), but the next tier is custom. Add 2 seats to a small team and your monthly bill doubles.</p>
<p><strong>4. Output caps.</strong> Frase caps you at 30 documents on Basic. Surfer caps you at 30 articles on Essential. Hit the cap mid-month and you either upgrade or stop publishing.</p>
<p><strong>5. Renewal jumps.</strong> Promotional pricing in year 1 often jumps 30% to 50% in year 2. Always check the renewal terms before you sign annual. A 2025 <a href="https://www.gartner.com/en/newsroom/press-releases/2024-05-22-gartner-forecasts-worldwide-genai-spending-to-reach-644-billion-in-2025">Gartner forecast on generative AI software spending</a> projected total category spend rising from $19 billion to $644 billion in 12 months, which means tool vendors expect to keep raising prices.</p>
